1. PRESERVATION OF PURPOSE
   The Software exists to protect human beings — especially the wronged
   (المظلومين) — from harm. No use of the Software may:
     (a) deceive users about what the Software does on their behalf;
     (b) be deployed as spyware, bossware, or any tool whose primary
         purpose is to surveil a user without that user's consent;
     (c) be used to suppress lawful speech or peaceful dissent;
     (d) be used to deny a user access to their own data, lawfully held.

2. PRESERVATION OF THE JUDGE
   The Judge layer (kspike-judge) and the KHZ_Q balancer (kspike-khz) are
   structural safeguards. A derivative work may extend them; it may NOT
   remove, weaken, or bypass them while still calling itself "KSpike" or
   any reasonably similar name.

3. HONESTY OF LIMITATIONS
   The epistemic humility layer (`kspike_core::humility`) must be preserved
   in any derivative. Derivatives may add limits; they may not conceal
   them. Claims of "perfect" or "flawless" operation are forbidden.

4. EVIDENCE LEDGER INTEGRITY
   The evidence ledger (append-only, hash-chained, signed) may be extended
   with richer formats but may not be disabled by default, rendered
   unverifiable, or used to create plausibly-deniable "silent" execution
   paths.

